text: Rianna Tei Valdes (born 3 September 1996) is an American tennis player. Valdes has a career-high WTA singles ranking of 498, achieved on 11 May 2015. She also has a career-high WTA doubles ranking of 434, set on 25 November 2019. Valdes won her first ITF title at the 2019 Thoreau Tennis Open in the doubles draw partnering Angela Kulikov.
